Hey, man.  Chill...<br>
<br>
You will have a hard time finding a Zerk or Shadowblade that will tell you there was nothing wrong with the damage output of Left Axe pre-1.62.  In fact, most will tell you, yeah, it could use a little tweaking.<br>
<br>
Cutting it almost in half was way overboard, and you know it.  That is no way to tune a spec line, and a single-line respec to EVERYBODY when nerfing a class is a joke.<br>
<br>
There are several reasons why the Berserker community was up in arms over 1.62:<br>
<br>
1)  Aurora Borealis was changed from a reactionary style to third in the chain of a behind style.  Ever try to get a behind style off in RvR?  How about one that is third in a chain?  For a LEVEL 50 spec style?  Ok, maybe you have gotten off a few behind positionals, but how about after 1.62 where they nerfed that too?<br>
<br>
2)  Damage across the board was reduced 40%, but endurance costs for the anytime style is still on the level of a shield slam.<br>
<br>
3)  Our primary buffing class got the nerf bat across the forehead.  Instead of being behind the lines, healing and what-not, they have to be right up there with us.  The Shaman, while having chain armor, has very low defense and isn't a tank-like class... it's a caster class.<br>
<br>
4)  The nerf was done without the input of a legitimate class team lead.  Ragnarthruu took pity on us and tried to offer input to the development team.  Apparently, even that was ignored.<br>
<br>
5)  The Blademaster's Tri-Weild totally negates Frenzy.<br>
<br>
6)  Both the Mercenary and Blademaster special abilities were boosted, while Frenzy was reduced (see 5.)<br>
<br>
I have nothing but good things to say about Blademaster and Mercenaries.  Mythic has needed to address dual weild issues since the game was released.  Why haven't they fixed you yet?  Easy.  Infiltrators and Nightshades.  If they put CW and DW on pre-1.62 LA levels, there would be no reason to play any other class.  Why did Shadowblades have this power?  Ask Mythic.  They're the ones that made Left Axe available to them.  They're also the ones that <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>BOOSTED</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Left Axe growth rates pre 1.62.<br>
<br>
Remember...  Mythic doesn't lie, and they know what they're doing.<br>
